TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;


## (a) ##

do {
  $e1 = random(-6,-2,1);
  $e2 = $e1 + random(2,8,2);

  $b1 = -$e1 - $e2;
  $c1 = $e1 * $e2;
} while ($b1 == 0 || $c1 == 0);

$b1h = $b1 / 2;
$u1 = "x^2 + $b1 x + $c1";

$du1 = "x + $b1h";

$f1 = "($du1)e^{$u1}";

$a = $e1 + random(-1,1,1);
$b = $e2 + random(-1,1,1);

$aa = ($a)**2 + $b1*($a) + $c1;
$bb = ($b)**2 + $b1*($b) + $c1;

#### Answers ####

$ans = (1/2)*(exp($bb) - exp($aa));


#################

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
Evaluate the definite integral.
$BR $BR
\( \displaystyle \int_{$a}^{$b} $f1 \, dx = \)
\{ ans_rule(40) \}
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS(num_cmp($ans));

BEGIN_SOLUTION 
Substitute \(u = g(x) = $u1\).  Then \(du = (2x + $b1)
\,dx = 2(x + $b1h) \,dx\). Use \(g(x)\) to change the limits of
integration.
\[ 
   \begin{array}{rcl} 
     \displaystyle \int_{$a}^{$b} $f1 \, dx &=&
     \displaystyle \dfrac{1}{2} 
     \int_{($a)^2 + $b1($a) + $c1}^{($b)^2 + $b1($b) + $c1} 
     e^u \, du \\ 
     &=& \dfrac{1}{2} e^u \Big|_{$aa}^{$bb}\\ 
     &=& \dfrac{1}{2}\left[ e^{$bb} - e^{$aa}\right]\\
     &=& $ans.
   \end{array} 
\] 
END_SOLUTION

